1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 20.1-02-04 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to positive detections of chronic wasting disease.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 20.1-02-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 20.1-02-04. Duties of director.
7 The director shall:
8 1. Maintain an office in Bismarck.
9 2. Adopt rules necessary to the conduct of the department.
10 3. Keep an accurate record of all the transactions and expenditures of the department
11 and submit a biennial report to the governor and the secretary of state in accordance
12 with section 54-06-04.
13 4. Enforce state laws involving wildlife.
14 5. Collect and distribute statistics and information germane to this title and publish
15 information and reports, including a monthly bulletin, for the education of the public in
16 conservation matters.
17 6. Examine all waters of the state and, wherever suitable waters are found, arrange to
18 plant, stock, or deposit available fish, spawn, or fry.
19 7. Cooperate with the United States fish and wildlife service, or any other appropriate
20 federal agency, and make applications for fish, spawn, and fry, to apportion and
21 deposit in waters of the state.
22 8. Cooperate with and assist clubs and individuals in stocking the waters of this state
23 with fish.
