1 9. Remove or take from any public waters containing a surplus of fish any reasonable
2 quantity of fish for stocking other public waters, hatching or propagating purposes, or
3 exchange with other states and countries.
4 10. Control, construct, mark, designate, manage, and have charge of all state fish
5 hatcheries, state game farms, game refuges, and game reserves owned, leased, or
6 controlled for the propagation and protection of game birds, game animals, and fish.
7 11. Supervise the breeding, propagation, capture, distribution, and preservation of game
8 birds, game animals, and fish as the director deems advisable.
9 12. Adopt rules necessary for carrying out section 20.1-10-01 and these rules have the
10 force of law after one publication in the daily newspapers of this state.
11 13. Provide the necessary blank forms for making applications for licenses of all kinds and
12 distribute them among those authorized to sell licenses.
13 14. Keep a record of all permits issued for the purpose of propagation and domestication
14 of game birds or protected animals.
15 15. Keep a record of and make available to the public all positive detections of chronic
16 wasting disease for four years, including a microscopic slide of the prion and necropsy
17 report.
